{"id":569235,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nigel_Rodley","text":"Sir Nigel Simon Rodley (1 December 1941 \u2013 25 January 2017) was a British human rights activist, lawyer and professor. He was a member of the United Nations Human Rights Committee. He was also a commissioner for the International Commission of Jurists. He held academic positions at the University of Essex and the London School of Economics.\nHe was of Jewish descent.\nRodley died after a short illness on 25 January 2017 in Colchester, at the age of 75.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Sir","surface_form":"Sir","offset":0},{"uri":"British_people","surface_form":"British","offset":65},{"uri":"Human_rights","surface_form":"human rights","offset":73},{"uri":"Activist","surface_form":"activist","offset":86},{"uri":"Lawyer","surface_form":"lawyer","offset":96},{"uri":"Professor","surface_form":"professor","offset":107},{"uri":"United_Nations","surface_form":"United Nations","offset":141},{"uri":"United_Nations_Human_Rights_Committee","surface_form":"Human Rights Committee","offset":156},{"uri":"International_Commission_of_Jurists","surface_form":"International Commission of Jurists","offset":215},{"uri":"Academic","surface_form":"academic","offset":260},{"uri":"University_of_Essex","surface_form":"University of Essex","offset":286},{"uri":"London_School_of_Economics","surface_form":"London School of Economics","offset":314},{"uri":"Jewish","surface_form":"Jewish","offset":352},{"uri":"Colchester","surface_form":"Colchester","offset":424}]}